	(text "- VDD has 7 capacitors because:\n    - 3 VDD pins\n    - 2 VDDIO3 pins\n    - 2 VDDIO4 pins\n- VDDCORE has 6 capacitors because:\n    - 5 VDDCORE pins\n    - 1 VDDCSI pin\n- VDDA1V8 has 4 capacitors because:\n    - Powering ADC, USB, PLL, and CSI\n\n- Power input to BOARD is 5V @ 3A max\n- Total of 5 LDOs and Bucks for 3v3 and 1v8\n    - Buck converter for 3v3 VDD, always on\n    - LDO for 1v8 VDDA18AON, always on\n    - LDO for 3v3 VDD3V3 (USB pin)\n    - LDO for 1v8 VDDA1V8\n    - LDO for 1v8 VDD1V8\n- All LDO's and Bucks should be adjustable\n   and with enable pins. Permanently enable\n   VDD and VDDA18AON. Others enabled by\n   PWR_ON.\n\n- Ferrite bead (FB1) requirements:\n    - 50 Ohms at 100MHz\n    - At least 400mA I_DC\n    - Max 0.1 Ohms DCR\n\n- VREFP is reference for internal ADC.\n   J1 is a jumper to VDDA1V8, use separate\n   reference if desired.\n\n- Forgot to add in symbols:\n    - LDO's are SPX5205-ADJ\n    - Buck is MC34064-ACD-TR\n    - Schottky diode is 1A 40V per the\n       datasheet. Preferably 1206 package\n    - Ferrite will be ILB1206ER500V\n\n- All decoupling caps will be 1206 imperial\n- All resistors will be 0805 imperial\n- TVS diode clamping voltages must not\n   exceed 1.935 and 3.6V clamping for 1v8\n   and 3v3 supplies respectively."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 229.87 24.13 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "3586df9d-9384-4030-bd01-de84602cac25")
	)
